Distributed System design for Big Data Systems course project.

The core idea is to build a framework for simulating real world physical distributed systems.
The first attempt at this system was the GPS constellation in the Summer - Fall of 2025.
I am now moving on to a more ambitious project in Simulating the multiple satellite constellations,
first and foremost is the StarLink constellation. 
This constellation is growing by the day, has over 9000 satellites in orbit, and presents unique 
challenges when compared to the Older and higher-up constellations like the GPS constellation. 

Since there are 9000 satellites, propagating their orbits with maximum precision represents a high
efficiency/performance task for an individual developer in his homelab. 

The requirements for the project are that I am working with gigabytes worth of data and
taking advantage of the HDFS ecosystem to operated on a big data distributed system.